Doll Tireman one of the Does in the Park, having met with three or four easy Cullies with Pockets well Lined, had made them Bleed freely, and Bubbled them of about half a score Guinny-spankers, which Mrs. Jilt the Reverend Matron, in whose house she Plyed, would needs have Sequestred to her own use, pretending a Debt for Cloaths, besides mony that she stood engaged for to the Doctor and Apothecary for the last new Rigging; But Doll. was Resolute not to part with a souce of her Col
   •
, whereupon began a very grave and civil Dialogue between them;
